{"lemma":"تَلِيدٌ","slug":"تَلِيدٌ","root":"ت.ل.د","root_slug":"ت-ل-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ل-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4034"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4034","headword_ar":"تَلِيدٌ","root":"tld","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tilaAdN","text_ar":"تِلَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-  Also That"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is born at the abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"home, of another than thyself, and which, while young, thou afterwards purchasest, and which remains with thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T.) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is born in a foreign country, and is carried away while young to the territory of the Arabs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is born in a foreign country, and then brought away while young, and who grows up in the territory of the Muslims;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taladN","text_ar":"تَلَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwal~adN","text_ar":"مُوَلَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwal~adapN","text_ar":"مُوَلَّدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [masc. and fem.,] meaning one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is born at thine own abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"home:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, T: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tilaAdN","text_ar":"تِلَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has parents at thine own abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"home;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whereas"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwal~adN","text_ar":"مُوَلَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies one who has only one parent there: (Mgh, from the Tekmileh [of the 'Eyn]:) the fem. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) signifying a female slave"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is born in a foreign country, and is carried away, and grows up in the territory of the Arabs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kt, T:) or a female slave"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose father and family and all her relations are in one country and who is herself in another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wld","text_ar":"ولد"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or a female slave"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"born the property of a people with whom are her parents:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wld","text_ar":"ولد"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or a female slave"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inherited by her owner;"},{"kind":"text","text":"if born at his own abode, or home, [of a mother already belonging to him,] she is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliydapN","text_ar":"وَلِيدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, L:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN taliydN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ تَلِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuladaA='u","text_ar":"تُلَدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN taliydN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ تَلِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taliydapN","text_ar":"تَلِيدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talaAy^idu","text_ar":"تَلَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, L) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuludN","text_ar":"تُلُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lh, L.) It is related in a trad. of Shureyh, that a man purchased a female slave, and the two parties made it a condition that she should be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwal~adap","text_ar":"مُوَلَّدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the purchaser found her to be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taliydap","text_ar":"تَلِيدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and therefore returned her: (S, Mgh:) a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwal~adap","text_ar":"مُوَلَّدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tilaAd","text_ar":"تِلَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. born at thine own abode, or home; (S;) or born in the territory of the Muslims. (Mgh.) ―         -b3-  Also, metaphorically, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A child,"},{"kind":"text","text":"absolutely. (Har p. 317.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","K","Kt","T","L","Lh","M","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}